{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow people to vote against petitions they disagree with.",
        "additional_details": "If 100,000 people agree with a petition and vote for it but millions disagree strongly there is no easy way for those millions to indicate this. Even setting up a petition saying the exact opposite does not tie the two together to allow an easy check. A simple \u201creject\u201d or \u201cdisagree\u201d option alongside the \u201csupport\u201d option would solve this.",
        "background": "There should be the ability to vote against petitions on this site so that people not only get to see how many people agree with a petition enough to vote but also how many people disagree.",
